File: load-shedding JOHANNESBURG - Eskom has confirmed that load-shedding will be suspended from 11pm on Monday night. The power utility says the generation capacity has improved following the return to service of some generation units. READ: COVID-19 negatively impacting Eskom Two more units are expected to be repaired and up and running by Tuesday. While load-shedding is set to be suspended, Eskom urged the public to use electricity sparingly. It said the risk of load-shedding remains high.